9199,IssuesEvent,2017-10-16 16:15:48+00:00,91284550,studioml/studio,1184005,karlmutch,30937953,studioml,closed,Job submission only partially configures GPU jobs,[],[{'login': 'karlmutch', 'id': 1184005, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1184005?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/karlmutch', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"The python job submission for example sets the gpu resources needed but fails to select the tensorflow-gpu pip install and uses only the CPU version of TensorFlow.  This is forcing runners to make assumptions.  The runner should be implementing mechanisms, not policy and so the studioml client needs to be changed to select appropriate pip installs rather than leaving it to the runners.",{},{}
